Pantomime
deck: Artificial demon no. 9 created by Franken Stein. He is obsessed with with raw power, and kills demons in order to steal their body-part so that he can grow more powerful.
description:
Before he became a monster, Pantomime was a demon with the power to mimic other demons magic abilities. He was the errand-boy of king Wolf Daddy.

One day, he was ordered to travel to the Human World and return with Wolf Daddy's former lover; Katy. He mimics the dimension-traveling magic of Heads Hydra, and summons the portal known as "The Black Curtain." But he never get's to the Human World since he is killed by Braz Blood. The portal is left opened, which allows the human Fuyumi to enter the Demon World.

Braz takes the dead body of Pantomime and gives it to Franken Stein, a scientist who tries to create demons out of dead ones. He manege to resurrect Pantomime, who are now known as Akim Papradon, AKA "Artificial Demon No. 9." Akim has no memories of his life as Pantomime, and all that interest him is to replace his, as he calls them himself, "poor body-parts," and grow stronger. He then escapes the lab by the use of the dimension-traveling magic he still has.

Akim travels around the Lower Demon World and kill whoever he finds with a body-part he likes, and ad the new one to his grotesque body. Eventually, he is stopped by Staz Blood, who almost kills him. Akim manege to escape death, but is captured by Bell Hydra. For all his crimes, Akim(as well as his creator Franken) is sent to the Demon World jail; Liz's Toy Box. In the jail, Akim's heart is removed from his body in order to resurrect he former king of the Demon World; Richarz Blood. It was believed that his body was an empty shell, but his body still managed to absorb a tiny amount of magic, and after some time, Akim could move his body again. He then uses his dimensional magic to get back his heart from Richarz Blood, and even drink all of his blood too, getting all of his magical abilities.

Powers & Abilities

Akim is actually a phantom, and does not have an actual body. Like a puppeteer, he uses magic to manipulate the dead body he poses. This means that he can get rid of, for example, an arm and replace it with a new one. Since the dead flesh that makes his body is moved by magic, it doesn't mater if a leg or arm is broken, he can still move it around, and he also feels no pain. The only way Akim can die is if he runs dry of magic.

Akim's first original ability is power-mimicking, which allow him to copy another demons magic, but to a lesser degree. This is how he can use dimensional magic, which allow him to create a portal to anywhere he wants to go.

Akim has recently killed and stolen the powers of Richarz Blood. He now has an aura that absorbs the magic of other demons and he can use this magic to boost his amount of magic, or give it to others by simply touching them. He can also materialize his magic outside his body.

Do to his ability to control dead flesh, he can bring corpses to live and fuel them with magic, thus creation artificial demons.

At the moment; Akim power-level is 193020 organ(a normal demon's organ is 3000).
name: Papradon Akim

べロス巡査
Officer Beros
deck: Police chief, and Goyles partner. As a member of the Acropolis police, he is in charge of peace and order in the Demon World.
description:
Beros is very rude, is usually never seen without a piece of gum in her mouth, and apparently has a great disliking of Braz Blood. She is on friendly terms with her partner Captain Goyle. Besides working for the Demon World police, she is also the guitarist in a band called "Evil Potato."

Powers & Abilities

Beros has the magic known as "Underdog Choker." It causes a dog collar to appear around a persons neck, and if the person attempts to use magic, he or she will get attacked by a big dog-like creature made out of flames. The collar also drain the person of a great amount of his/her magic. he collar can only be removed if Beros allows it.
name: Constable Beros

deck: The king of Demon World Acropolis. He is the father of Wolf.
description:
Wolf Daddy was a good friend of Richarz Blood. Instead of his son, Richarz decided to make Wolf Daddy his heir to the throne.

One day, Herrschaft Grimm's magi got out "the Door of Magical Essence". Wolf Daddy and Richarz, as well as Richarz wife, fought the materialized magic in order to force it back through the door before in spread chaos in the Demon World. They managed to do this, but not without Richarz's wife being dragged in as well, and Richarz had to absorb some of the magic as well. Knowing that Grimm's magic would live on in him, he asked Wolf Daddy to kill him. Wolf Daddy does so, by pulling his heart out of his body. Richarz's son Braz watches his father's dead, believing that Wolf Daddy killed him so that he could take his throne.

At some point, Wolf Daddy had a affair with a demon called Katy. It is unknown if she left him before the birth of their son Wolf. After Wolf were born, Katy left the Demon world in order to live as a human, and Wolf was then left to be raised by his father. Wolf Daddy abounded him quickly, do to his son being a half-bread, and made his son life as a low-class demon, despite him being son of the king.

Powers & Abilities

Wolf Daddy is a werewolf, and possibly the most powerful demon in the Demon World(until Akim took his throne).

Wolf Daddy can use his magic to increase his strength, and he can also use his magic to turn into werewolf form, which makes him several times even stronger. the werewolf form also grants him claws that can cut through anything and create shock-waves.

Unlike other werewolves who only use their magic to make their bodies stronger, Wolf Daddy is also capable of using energy based attacks. His finishing move is called "Obedience Laser", where he summons dozen of energy balls that all fires off lasers, pulverizing Wolf Daddy's enemy.
name: Wolf Daddy

deck:
A huge dragon-like demon, who can also take the form of a human. He is the husband of Neyn and father to Bell and Knell.
He can move, control and create space as he is pleased.
description:
Once when his wife visited the Human World with their daughter Bell, she met her doppelganger. Therefor, the two women was combined into one woman due to magic, and became the woman known as Neyn. After a long debate between Heads and Mr. Yanagi, whom he now shared his wife with, Yanagi decided that it would be best if his daughter Fuyumi was raised in the Human World, so Heads could take her home. But before he when home, Yanagi swore to him that if he ever made his wife unhappy, then he would have to answer to him. Realizing that Yanagi was dead serious, Heads was afraid for the first time in his life, and he therefor has respect for Yanagi.

He gained a son with Neyn, whom they called Knell.

Sometime later, he showed his dimensional magic to the king Wolf Daddy, and is therefor partly to blame for the dead of Fuyumi, since one of the kings trusted men, named Pantomime, copied his magic, an opened the portal that brought Fuyumi to the Demon World.

When his wife's pen-pal, Braz Blood, wrote a email the claimed that his brother Staz was going to drink Fuyumi's blood, Neyn wanted to get her daughter away from Staz, and make her live with her. But Heads, not wanting to make Yanagi more unhappy than he already had made him by taking his wife, decided to help Staz and Fuyumi to escape, but only after "cursing" Staz(the curse is fake, but Staz buys it).

Powers & Abilities

Heads can change from human to dragon with ease. He prefer his human-form, if he has to speak with someone, since he can look them in the eyes that way.

Heads magic allow him to manipulate space as he please. He can move himself and others through it, and create all the space he wants.

Heads also has wings that allows him flight, colossal strength, and claws.
name: Heads Hydra

deck: Goth student at the King’s Dominion School of the Deadly Arts.
description:
History

Petra is a gloomy goth girl who begins to date Marcus Lopez during the Kids of the Black Hole arc. Her parents were both hippies who joined a death cult and met Master Lin at an orgy. They figured a way to relieve themselves of their parent duties with Petra was to dump her off at Lin's school, King's Dominion Atelier of the Deadly Arts. On Petra's 11th Birthday she found a mason jar with her mother's eye balls in the fridge. Her father explained that he had watched her mother die and that witnesses such a thing gives you strength and strips away your fear. Shortly after this, Petra went away to school.

Petra first met Marcus on top of a roof at King's Dominion. She was hanging out with Willie, Billy, Dan and Lex. Some time later, when Marcus was rejected by his friends, she invited him to hang out with her. Eventually, the two hooked up as Marcus continued his downward spiral of shame and worried about his friend turning against him.

When Master Lin soon announced the semester's final was to kill all the rats, those that have disobeyed the school's rules, both Marcus and Petra realized they had been labelled as rats. Marcus grabbed Petra and the two attempted to flee from their classmates. Petra concocted poison to help them kill several classmates that were pursuing them. They then grabbed Billy along the way, who agreed it was safer to be with his kind, the rats, then to be with others. Elsewhere, Viktor teamed up with Shabnam as they made plans to hunt down and kill Marcus.

They made a plan to kill Viktor. When Paulie bailed on them, Billy was chased and was left to improvise. Marcus and Petra caught up with Billy as the trap and found Billy had been beaten savagely. Viktor was sprawled out on the ground as the gigantic stone they rigged had fallen and smashed Viktor in the back. However, they were soon attacked by an explosive arrow. They escaped to the last place anyone would look for the three of them, F-face's old place, the Tenderloin. Marcus finally agreed with Billy and Petra to run from the school and stop playing this deadly game.

Name Confusion

The character was originally introduced in issue 2 of Deadly Class. She had a limited role and was referred to as Yolga. The character was reintroduced in issue 7 as Petra.While the series has never mentioned the name confusion, Wes Craig has confirmed they are the same person.
name: Yolga
